modules.description: This module provides functions to convert basic OCaml values such as `unit`, `bool`, `int`, `float`, and `string` into pretty-printable documents. It supports structured data types like `option`, `list`, and tuples through combinators that recursively format their contents. Use this module to generate readable string representations of complex OCaml data structures for debugging or logging.

This module provides functions to pretty-print the internal structure of documents before and after rendering. It works with the `SmartPrint.t` type to visualize layout transformations, such as space-to-newline replacements. Use it to debug document formatting by inspecting structural changes at different stages of the rendering pipeline.

This module offers document formatting operations for pretty-printing, combining text elements with layout control through indentation, grouping, and delimiter enclosure. It works with documents represented as `SmartPrint.t`, supporting operations like concatenation, separation, and enclosure in parentheses or braces, while handling spaces and newlines explicitly. The module is used to convert OCaml values into structured text outputs, debug document layouts, and render results to strings, buffers, or channels with customizable formatting parameters like width and tab size.
